event: Here is the table of events and timestamps:
numbness and weakness in lower extremities
albuminocytologic dissociation in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF)
flaccid paralysis of all four extremities
provisional diagnosis of AIDP complicated by septic shock
diffuse slow waves consistent with severe metabolic encephalopathy
hyperintensity of the bilateral medial thalamus on T2-weighted and fluid-attenuated inversion recovery (FLAIR) axial images
mentation and weakness continued to gradually improve
transferred out of the intensive care unit (ICU)
